You want to loop over the contents of a file. Best to do this is a `for /f` loop. But you don&#39;t even need a file. Just loop over all `*_v1.mxf` files instead. Then split the movie name and add all `&lt;MovieName_a*&gt;` file names:

    @echo off
    setlocal enabledelayedexpansion
    
    for %%a in (*_v1.*) do (
      set &quot;all=&quot;%%a&quot;&quot;
      for /f &quot;delims=_&quot; %%b in (&quot;%%~na&quot;) do (
        for %%c in (&quot;%%b_*a*&quot;) do set all=!all! &quot;%%c&quot;
      )
      echo !all!
    )

If for any reason you really need to loop over a file, replace the first `for %%a` loop with a `for /f &quot;delims=&quot; %%a in (file.txt) do (`
